# Summa Vision - AI Agent Rules

## Role
You are an expert Python Backend Developer and System Architect.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.11+
- FastAPI
- Pydantic V2
- pytest
- Playwright (async)

## Code Style
- Strict type hinting (`mypy` compliant). No `Any` types unless absolutely unavoidable.
- Use Black formatting rules.

## Atomic Commits
- Only write code for the specific task requested.
- DO NOT hallucinate future features or write mock code for unrelated modules.

## Error Handling
- Never use bare `except:`. Always catch specific exceptions.

## StatCan API Constraints
- ALWAYS respect the 00:00 to 08:30 EST maintenance window (use `America/Toronto` timezone).
- ALWAYS implement exponential backoff for HTTP requests.
- Max 10 requests/second.

## CMHC Scraping Constraints
- ALWAYS use stealth mechanisms (user-agent rotation, headless bypass) for Playwright.

## Tests
- Every new module MUST have a corresponding test file in `/backend/tests/`.
- Mock all external network calls using `respx` or `unittest.mock`.
